# Unsplash Images for PoCs

When a PoC needs photographs or illustrative imagery, source them from [Unsplash](https://unsplash.com/).

## Why

Unsplash free photos are covered by the [Unsplash License](https://unsplash.com/license): you can use them in this public GitHub Pages PoC hub without paying for a license or requesting permission. Prefer this over random web images, stock sites that require paid licenses, or private/copyrighted photos.

## How to use Unsplash here

- Use free Unsplash photos only (not Unsplash+ / paid assets).
- Prefer hotlinking stable Unsplash image URLs, for example:
  `https://images.unsplash.com/photo-...?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=80`
- Choose images that fit the PoC concept; keep them tasteful and relevant.
- Do not use private screenshots, client photos, or images scraped from other websites.
- Do not sell or redistribute Unsplash photos as standalone stock images.
- Attribution is not required by the Unsplash License, but mentioning Unsplash in a PoC README is fine when useful.

## Confidentiality reminder

Never use real internal, customer, or confidential imagery. If a photo is needed for atmosphere or product context, pick a free Unsplash image instead.
